You're missing the `BindingContext`. The `{Binding}` markup requires it to know *what object* to bind against. Set it in your code-behind:

```csharp
public partial class MyPage : ContentPage
{
    public MyPage(MyViewModel vm)
    {
        InitializeComponent();
        BindingContext = vm;
    }
}
```

Or in XAML (if the VM has a parameterless constructor):

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns:local="clr-namespace:YourApp.ViewModels"
             ...>
    <ContentPage.BindingContext>
        <local:MyViewModel />
    </ContentPage.BindingContext>
    ...
</ContentPage>
```

Also verify your ViewModel implements `INotifyPropertyChanged` (or uses `[ObservableProperty]` from the MVVM Community Toolkit) so the UI updates when property values change.
